#  Bash Scripting 

Bash is the default command-line shell for most Unix-like systems. It acts both as a command interpreter and a scripting language, enabling users to automate tasks and interact with the operating system efficiently. Bash is an enhanced version of the original Bourne shell.
This guide provides a **well-structured beginner → intermediate flow** for learning Bash scripting.

---

